        "created_at": "2017-04-03T20:59:38.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Rob Weaver\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n Rob Weaver:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Going to Napa from 4/20-4/27.  Will be cycling in the mornings and hitting a winery or two in the afternoons.</p>\n<p>Would like to do between 25 and 40 miles for the morning rides (minor exposure to Oakville Grade!), so if you can link me to some good routes, it would be appreciated.  Also, a good bike shop to rent decent quality road bikes from would be great.</p>\n<p>As to wineries, I have been to Napa many times and I have fallen into a rut of just going to the same old places, would like to mix it up a bit this time.  I\u2019m only interested in Cab and blends, maybe a decent Chardonnay, but no Syrah or Pinot.</p>\n<p>My favorite cab producers are Forman, Togni, Spottswoode, Corison, Kapcsandy, Mayacamas. I also like the Mondavi and Beringer reserves on occasion. I loved the old Arrowood Reserve bottlings.  I have been to all of the above plus, Realm, VHR, Blankiet, Larkmead, Ramey, Shafer, Phelps, Montelena, Myriad/Quivet, Fisher, David Arthur, Outpost.</p>\n<p>So far I have only scheduled Roy Piper.  Would love some other referrals.</p>\n<p>Thanks in advance.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Get in touch with Jean Hoffliger here - he\u2019s the winemaker at Alpha Omega and sets up a killer tasting.</p>",
