      {
        "id": 2158213,
        "name": "Robert Ferguson",
        "username": "Robert_Ferguson",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/r/958977/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2017-04-04T13:13:15.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I\u2019ve rented bikes from Calistoga Bike Shop. <a href=\"http://calistogabikeshop.com\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">http://calistogabikeshop.com</a></p>\n<p>If you\u2019re a climber, there are some great climbs in the area. The bike shop can help. I\u2019ve done Howell Mountain a couple of times.</p>\n<p>Cliff Family Winery is really into biking and has several routes on their site, all of which look interesting.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.cliffamily.com/cycling-adventures/\" class=\"onebox\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">http://www.cliffamily.com/cycling-adventures/</a></p>\n<p>For a flatish route there\u2019s the Silverado Trail. The locals consider it only OK due to the traffic, but it didn\u2019t bother me. The bike shop gave me a another flatfish route heading north out of Calistoga on 128 and then meandering on some side roads for a bit.</p>\n<p>My favorite winery to visit is Beringer. I like the history of the place and enjoy the Reserve tasting.</p>\n<p>Robert</p>",
