      {
        "id": 2158233,
        "name": "Robert R",
        "username": "Robert_R",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/robert_r/{size}/2092_2.png",
        "created_at": "2017-04-04T13:56:57.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>My wife and I ride out in Napa every Spring. The Silverado Trail is great road that you can easily ride 60-80 miles or more with wide shoulders for the vast majority of the ride. All along the way are roads that run perpendicular into the various towns (Oakville, Yountville, St. Helena, etc\u2026) that are also good riding with little traffic and you can use to get to your various lunch/winery destinations. Skellenger Lane is just one such example, a nice low traffic road that runs by one of the large Beckstoffer properties and Caymus.  Howell Mountain road is a more challenging ride, but much easier than Oakville Grade, and takes you to all of the Howell Mountain vineyards (Arkenstone, Cade, etc\u2026) Also, the Old Howell Mountain Road is a wonderful zero traffic road.<br>\nSt. Helena Cyclery are nice guys that I\u2019ve used and have been 100% reliable.</p>",
        "post_number": 6,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 8,
        "updated_at": "2022-06-02T22:32:35.001Z",
